==English==
===Noun===
'''axiom''', plural '''[[axioms]]'''

#A self-evident and necessary truth, or a [[proposition]] whose truth is so evident at first sight that no reasoning or demonstration can make it plainer; a proposition which it is necessary to take for granted.
#: "The whole is greater than a part;" 
#: "A thing can not both be and not be at the same time and in the same respect."
#: "No one gives what he does not have."
#An established [[principle]] in some art or science, which, though not a necessary truth, is universally received; as, the axioms of political economy.

